    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-01T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-01T14:00:00-05:00" n="983"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d983">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 LCC/23: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-01T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 1, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3484. For Bucknell, reference Embassy’s despatch No. 14, 940, April 8, 1944.<note
                        n="18" xml:id="d983fn18">Not printed, but see footnote 17, <ref
                            target="#pg_1462">p. 1462</ref>.</note> We have concluded that it would
                    be unwise to press the Soviet Government further with regard to membership on
                    the London Propaganda Coordinating Committee. In commenting upon Ambassador
                    Harriman’s several inquiries regarding the Soviet Government’s attitude towards
                    the parallel American and British invitations to join the Committee, the Soviet
                    authorities have indicated that they regard the situation as very complex,
                    requiring much study and fraught with many obstacles. We are of the opinion that
                    we have done as much as we reasonably should in extending the invitation. The
                    door is open to the Soviet Government whenever it wishes to avail itself of the
                    Committee’s facilities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
